{"parse":{"title":"George Griffiths (historian)","pageid":57196500,"revid":853348607,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>\n<b>George John Griffiths</b> <a href=\"/wiki/Queen%27s_Service_Order\" title=\"Queen&#39;s Service Order\">QSO</a> (1933\u201329 January 2014) was a New Zealand historian, writer, and journalist.\n</p><p>Griffiths started his newspaper career in 1954 at the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Southland_Times\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Southland Times\">Southland Times</a></i>, based in <a href=\"/wiki/Invercargill\" title=\"Invercargill\">Invercargill</a>, moving to <a href=\"/wiki/Dunedin\" title=\"Dunedin\">Dunedin</a> and joining the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Otago_Daily_Times\" title=\"Otago Daily Times\">Otago Daily Times</a></i> in 1962. He was to work at the latter paper until his retirement in 1991.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ODT_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ODT-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In 1978, Griffiths co-founded <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Otago_Heritage_Books&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Otago Heritage Books (page does not exist)\">Otago Heritage Books</a>, which published books on the history of the southern <a href=\"/wiki/South_Island\" title=\"South Island\">South Island</a>, many of which were edited by Griffiths, and also operated as a central Dunedin bookshop which became a hub for local writers and historians.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> He also wrote numerous books, many of which were published by Otago Heritage Books, most of them relating to <a href=\"/wiki/History_of_Otago\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"History of Otago\">Otago history</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-ODT_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ODT-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and contributed many biographical articles to the <a href=\"/wiki/Dictionary_of_New_Zealand_Biography\" title=\"Dictionary of New Zealand Biography\">Dictionary of New Zealand Biography</a>.\n</p><p>Griffiths was named as a <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Otago\" title=\"University of Otago\">University of Otago</a> <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hocken_Fellowship&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Hocken Fellowship (page does not exist)\">Hocken fellow</a> in 1998.<sup id=\"cite_ref-commun_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-commun-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> He was also named Dunedin's Citizen of the Year in 1999, and in the same year was awarded a <a href=\"/wiki/Queen%27s_Service_Order\" title=\"Queen&#39;s Service Order\">Queen's Service Order</a> for services to the community, and was also awarded an honorary doctorate by the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Otago\" title=\"University of Otago\">University of Otago</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ODT_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ODT-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Griffiths died in early 2014. Many of his personal papers are now held as part of the <a href=\"/wiki/Hocken_Library\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hocken Library\">Hocken Library</a> collection.<sup id=\"cite_ref-commun_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-commun-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=George_Griffiths_(historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-ODT-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-ODT_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ODT_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ODT_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.odt.co.nz/news/dunedin/historian-dies-80\">Historian dies at 80</a>,\" <i><a href=\"/wiki/Otago_Daily_Times\" title=\"Otago Daily Times\">Otago Daily Times</a></i>, 30 January 2014. Retrieved 22 April 2018.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">McLean, Gavin \"<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://beattiesbookblog.blogspot.co.nz/2014/02/george-griffiths-rip.html\">George Griffiths R.I.P.</a>,' <i>Beattie's Book Blog \u2013 unofficial homepage of the New Zealand book community</i>, 3 February 2014. Retrieved 22 April 2018.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-commun-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-commun_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-commun_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://thecommunityarchive.org.nz/node/78779/description\">Griffiths, George John, Dr&#160;: Business, research and personal papers</a>,\" <i>thecommunityarchive.org.nz</i>. Retrieved 22 April 2018.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Flag_of_New_Zealand.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/Flag_of_New_Zealand.svg/30px-Flag_of_New_Zealand.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"15\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/Flag_of_New_Zealand.svg/45px-Flag_of_New_Zealand.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/Flag_of_New_Zealand.svg/60px-Flag_of_New_Zealand.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1200\" data-file-height=\"600\" /></a></td><td><i>This article about a New Zealand writer or poet is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a 